Source: lernstick-firefox-esr
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ronny Standtke <ronny.standtke@fhnw.ch>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7)
Standards-Version: 3.7.3

Package: lernstick-firefox-esr
Architecture: all
Depends: firefox-esr
Description: Changes the name in the firefox-esr desktop file
 We rename "Firefox ESR" back to just "Firefox". Our users do not care and are
 confused by the "ESR" suffix. Honestly, the development branch of a software
 should really not end up in its desktop file name entries.
 We also add PDF mimetypes to the desktop file. This fixes the following issue:
 https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1031041
